Let \Bbbk / \mathbb {L} and \mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F} be field extensions. Then \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {F})\supseteq \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}), i.e., we have a bijection  egin {split}\left \{ egin {matrix}\hbox {extensions }\mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F}\ \hbox {for }\mathbb {L} \subseteq \Bbbk \end {matrix}ight \}&\leftrightarrow \left \{ egin {matrix}\hbox {subgroups of }\ \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {F})\end {matrix}ight \}\ \mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F} &\mapsto \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L})\end {split} But this correspondence is order reversing in the sense that if \Bbbk \supseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\supseteq \mathbb {L}_{2}\supseteq \mathbb {F} we have \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1})\subseteq \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{2}).
